other_tests.findings: The appendix is hyperenhancing and enlarged, measuring up to 15 mm in diameter, with the proximal and mid portions of the appendix fluid filled. The more distal aspect of the appendix, however, appears collapsed with surrounding fluid raising a question of a microperforation. Dependent bibasilar atelectasis was observed, the heart size is normal, and the liver is otherwise normal in appearance with no free air or free fluid.
